msgstr "<p>Rood: 0-255</p><p>Groen: 0вБ†вАУвБ†255</p><p>Blauw: 0-255</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for hexadecimal code.
#: colordialog.cpp:195
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid ""
"<p>Hexadecimal color code, as used in HTML: #RRGGBB</p><p>RR: two-digit code "
"for red: 00вБ†вАУвБ†FF</p><p>GG: two-digit code for green: 00вБ†вАУвБ†FF</p><p>BB: two-digit "
"code for blue: 00вБ†вАУвБ†FF</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>Hexadecimale kleurcode, zoals gebruikt in HTML: #RRGGBB</p><p>RR: twee "
"cijferige code voor rood: 00вБ†вАУвБ†FF</p><p>GG: twee cijferige code voor groen: "
"00вБ†вАУвБ†FF</p><p>BB: twee cijferige code voor blauw: 00вБ†вАУвБ†FF</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for HSL (hue, saturation, lightness). Saturation: 0 means something on the grey axis; 255 means something between the grey axis and the most colorful color. This is different from вАЬchromaвАЭ and should therefore get a different translation. Lightness: 0 means always black; 255 means always white. This is different from вАЬbrightnessвАЭ and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:208
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid ""
"<p>Hue: 0¬∞вБ†вАУвБ†360¬∞</p><p>HSL-Saturation: 0%вБ†вАУвБ†100%</p><p>Lightness: 0%вБ†вАУвБ†100%</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>Tint: 0¬∞вБ†вАУвБ†360¬∞</p><p>HSL-verzadiging: 0%вБ†вАУвБ†100%</p><p>Lichtheid: 0%вБ†вАУвБ†100%</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for HWB (hue, whiteness, blackness). The idea behind is that the hue defines the pure (maximum colorful) color. Than, white color can be added, creating a вАЬtintвАЭ. Or black color can be added, creating a вАЬshadeвАЭ. Or both can be added, creating a вАЬtoneвАЬ. See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tint,_shade_and_tone for more information. 0% white + 0% black = pure color. 100% white + 0% black = white. 0% white + 100% black = black. 50% white + 50% black = gray. 50% white + 0% black = tint. 25% white + 25% black = tone. 0% white + 50% black = shade.
#: colordialog.cpp:222
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid "<p>Hue: 0¬∞вБ†вАУвБ†360¬∞</p><p>Whiteness: 0%вБ†вАУвБ†100%</p><p>Blackness: 0%вБ†вАУвБ†100%</p>"
msgstr "<p>Tint: 0¬∞вБ†вАУвБ†360¬∞</p><p>Witheid: 0%вБ†вАУвБ†100%</p><p>Zwartheid: 0%вБ†вАУвБ†100%</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for HSV/HSB. HSV (hue, saturation, value) and HSB (hue, saturation, brightness) are two different names for the very same color model. Saturation: 0 means something between black and white; 255 means something between black and the most colorful color. This is different from вАЬchromaвАЭ and should therefore get a different translation. Brightness/value: 0 means always black; 255 means something between white and the most colorful color. This is different from вАЬlightnessвАЭ and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:235
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid ""
"<p>Hue: 0¬∞вБ†вАУвБ†360¬∞</p><p>HSV/HSB-Saturation: 0%вБ†вАУвБ†100%</p><p>Brightness/Value: "
"0%вБ†вАУвБ†100%</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>Tint: 0¬∞вБ†вАУвБ†360¬∞</p><p>HSV/HSB-verzadiging: 0%вБ†вАУвБ†100%</p><p>Helderheid/waarde: "
"0%вБ†вАУвБ†100%</p>"

#. @label:slider Accessible name for lightness slider. This is different from вАЬbrightnessвАЭ/вАЬvalueвАЭ and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:246
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid "Lightness"
msgstr "Lichtheid"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for CIELCH. вАЬlightnessвАЭ is different from вАЬbrightnessвАЭ/вАЬvalueвАЭ and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:251
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid "<p>Lightness: 0%вБ†вАУвБ†100%</p><p>Chroma: 0вБ†вАУвБ†%L1</p><p>Hue: 0¬∞вБ†вАУвБ†360¬∞</p>"
msgstr "<p>Lichtheid: 0%вАУвБ†100вБ†%</p><p>Chroma: 0вБ†вАУвБ†%L1</p><p>Tint: 0¬∞вБ†вАУвБ†360¬∞</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for Oklch. вАЬlightnessвАЭ is different from вАЬbrightnessвАЭ/вАЬvalueвАЭ and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:260
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid ""
"<p>Lightness: %L1вБ†вАУвБ†%L2</p><p>Chroma: %L3вБ†вАУвБ†%L4</p><p>Hue: 0¬∞вБ†вАУвБ†360¬∞</"
"p><p>Whitepoint: D65</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>Lichtheid: %L1вБ†вАУвБ†%L2</p><p>Chroma: %L3вБ†вАУвБ†%L4</p><p>Tint: 0¬∞вБ†вАУвБ†360¬∞</"
"p><p>Witpunt: D65</p>"

#. @label:slider An opacity of 0 means completely transparent. The higher the opacity value increases, the more opaque the colour becomes, until it finally becomes completely opaque at the highest possible opacity value.
#: colordialog.cpp:273
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid "Op&acity:"
msgstr "D&ekking:"

